      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RIPPLES NZ (3) has been good in three Menangle starts so far this campaign including a fresh win from a wide barrier and a Listed placing after racing wide last time. Has built a terrific record at this distance and is two from two here having won both a heat and the final of last year's Gold Tiara. The good draw should give her every chance to maintain that perfect record. PERFECTDELIGHT (7) came from the outside barrier and finished just behind Ripples when fourth in the Raith Memorial last start. Had kicked off her campaign with a win at this circuit and distance prior. Threat. CAPTURE OUR HEART NZ (9) draws for a trail and did get close to a handy colt when runner-up two back at Wagga. Last-winner YIRRADIVA (10) has some upside and can get into the finish with even luck from the back row.",
